Sentencas: Low-temperature operation of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) results in deterioration in electrochemical performance due to sluggish oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) at the cathode.
Titulo: High-performance solid oxide fuel cells with fiber-based cathodes for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: To enhance the reaction pathway for ORR, La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 (LSM) nanofibers were fabricated by electrospinning and used for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells operated at 600-700 degrees C.
Titulo: High-performance solid oxide fuel cells with fiber-based cathodes for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: The morphological and structural characteristics show that the electrospun LSM nanofiber has a highly crystallized perovskite structure with a uniform elemental distribution.
Titulo: High-performance solid oxide fuel cells with fiber-based cathodes for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: The average diameter of the LSM nanofiber after sintering is 380 nm.
Titulo: High-performance solid oxide fuel cells with fiber-based cathodes for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: A symmetric cell of nanofiber-based LSM cathode on scandia-stabilized zirconia (SSZ) electrolyte pellet exhibits much lower area specific resistances compared to commercial LSM powder-based cathode.
Titulo: High-performance solid oxide fuel cells with fiber-based cathodes for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: A single cell based on the nanofiber LSM cathode on yttrium-doped barium cerate-zirconia (BCZY) electrolyte exhibits a power density of 0.35 Wcm(-2) at 600 degrees C, which increases to 0.85 Wcm(-2) at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: High-performance solid oxide fuel cells with fiber-based cathodes for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: The cell has an area specific resistance (ASR) of 0.46 Omega cm2 at 600 degrees C, which decreases to 0.07 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: High-performance solid oxide fuel cells with fiber-based cathodes for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: The results indicate that the LSM electrode fabricated by the electrospinning process produces a nanostructured porous electrode which optimizes the microstructure and significantly enhances the ORR at the cathode of SOFCs.
Titulo: High-performance solid oxide fuel cells with fiber-based cathodes for low-temperature operation
